description: Harry Osborn is back from S.H.I.E.L.D. custody, knows that Peter is Spider-Man and his vital role in defeating his father Norman ; Harry hallucinates about Shaw, his father's hitman, who goads him to unleash his “hidden abilities”; Harry transforms into the Hobgoblin; Peter fights Harry and is emotionally drained; Peter breaks up with Mary Jane because he realizes his superhero life will always endanger her.
name: Hobgoblin

description: The story of Orc Stain continues, as the agents of the great Orc Tzar finally catch up to One-Eye. Thousands of other one eyed orcs have been gathered to an arena by the mysterious Beard, who is hellbent on finding which of them is the key to unlocking the god organ...
name: V: Belly of the Beast

description: The mutant criminal lord known as Hammerhead tries to overthrow the Kingpin; Spider-Man suddenly is offered incriminating evidence about Hammerhead by Elektra and Kingpin; Black Cat shows up and pairs up with Spider-Man; after a gigantic fight, many characters are incapacitated; Black Cat breaks up with Spider-Man after discovering his age; it is revealed that every move has been subtly controlled by Kingpin's trusty pawn, the corrupt Jean De Wolfe.
name: Warriors

description:
Spider-Man beat Omega Red. Flash Thompson gets kidnapped by Silver Sable, thinking he is Spider-Man, who is wanted by the Roxxon Corporation for questioning; Spider-Man confronts Silver, but he is captured and brought to the Roxxon Corporation; The Vulture swoops in and is subdued by Spider-Man and Silver; the Tinkerer (Tinker-er) is revealed as the culprit, and Nick Fury finds him and tells him he will either work for him or go to jail, and hires him to work for S.H.I.E.L.D.

Also, Peter and Kitty Pryde, from the X-Men, become a couple.
name: Silver Sable

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Deadpool and his Reavers abduct Spider-Man and the X-Men to Genosha for a reality TV show in which they hunt down heroes; the X-Men and Spider-Man defeat them; back in New York, Aunt May has a good date with Miles Warren.
name: Deadpool

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Collects issues #97-105 of Ultimate Spider-Man.
name: Clone Saga

description:
Ultimate Daredevil attempts to enlist Spider-Man in a crusade to bring down the Kingpin -- permanently. But with his Aunt’s life hanging by a thread, and his serious girl problems with MJ and Kitty Pryde, crimebusting may be the last thing on young Mr. Parker’s mind.

Collects issues #106-111 of Ultimate Spider-Man.
name: Ultimate Knights

description: After Norman Osborn escapes his incarceration at the Triskelion, he tries to redeem his public image by attempting to convince Spider-Man to tell the world that he was created from the OZ formula that he invented. Carol Danvers decides to use his son, Harry, to draw him out. When Osborn attacks S.H.I.E.L.D., he causes Harry to transform into the Hobgoblin. After a brutal battle, Norman accidentally murders Harry by beating him to death. Osborn, sickened by what he's done, asks to be killed by S.H.I.E.L.D. Danvers gladly complies. In school, Peter gives Harry a eulogy, stating that in the end, he was a hero.
name: Volume 19

volume.name: Ultimate Spider-Man: Death of A Goblin

description:
Things are changing in the young life of Peter Parker: Johnny Storm of the Fantastic Four is now his buddy - and the hot-headed super hero has taken a liking to Peter's classmate, Liz Allen! But something is horribly wrong with Liz - something that will soon affect the life of every student at Midtown High - including Peter's ex-girlfriend, Kitty Pryde!

Collects issues 118-122 of Ultimate Spider-Man
name: Volume 20

volume.name: Ultimate Spider-Man: And His Amazing Friends

description:
Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #123-128.

Venom returns for the "War of the Symbiotes!" When Spidey's most fearsome foe strikes, it looks bad for the outmatched web-slinger, but Silver Sable and her Wild Pack may turn the tide! Have they come to save Spider-Man or is their motive something more sinister?
name: Volume 21

volume.name: Ultimate Spider-Man: War of the Symbiotes

description: Ultimatum is upon us! Big changes are afoot and with them comes the much-anticipated return of ULTIMATE SPIDER-WOMAN! But is she friend or foe? Plus, Aunt May is under arrest, Spider-Man is underwater, and the world has gone to hell. Spidey and the gang will never be the same! Guest- starring the Human Torch and Kitty Pryde! Collects Ultimate Spider-Man #129-133.
name: Volume 22

description: Meet Buddy Bradley, the alternative hero living, loving (but mostly bumming) around Seattle with his pals Stinky and George. The series starts off with a tour of their shared home, the perfect place for some serious drinking and thinking.
name: My Pad and Welcome To It!

description: All of the best of Peter Bagge from the year 2000 all in one place! First off, there's a Buddy and Lisa yarn (yay!), picking right up from Hate #30. Then, there's an eight-page story featuring the new Bagge character, "Lovey." Add in a whole slew of "comics journalism" pieces (watch out, Joe Sacco!) done for Suck.com (R.I.P.) and presented in print here for the very first time — on such subjects as the Infomercial Oscars, hopeless presidential hopeful Alan Keyes, and the Seattle Experience Music Project, all skewered with Bagge's trademark wit — plus such odds and ends as a three-page "Matrix" story, and you've got 48 pages of never-before-printed full-color Bagge for a great price!
name: Are You Nuts?

description: Written by JIMMY PALMIOTTI, JEFF PARKER, JOHN LUSTIG Penciled by JOHN BUSCEMA, DON HECK, JOHN ROMITA, GENE COLON Cover by AMANDA CONNER. Continuing the noble pursuit of taking funny old pictures and putting funny words on top of them! We've asked some of the funniest writers in comics today to look at the romance comics of yesteryear and put in some new dialogue that'll make us laugh! Unfortunately, the FUNNIEST writers were busy, so we had to settle on these guys. Hey, you get what you pay for!
name: The Diner Demon; Love Ain't Cheap...Especially At These Prices!; Formula For Love!; I Love Him--But He's Hers!; A (Former Child) Star Is Born!

description:
True Tales of the Greatest Lies Ever Told! 
 
THE BIG BOOK OF HOAXES is an entertaining encyclopedia of the most amazing deceptions, fables, and cons in the history of the world. Reporting on the unbelievable scams that have fooled people throughout time, this fascinating book documents the "true tales of the greatest lies ever told." From Orson Welles' War of the Worlds invasion to the actual sale of the Brooklyn Bridge to the woman who was impregnated by a six-foot rabbit, this black and white volume reveals just how gullible and manipulative man can be.

For a million millennia the world has cracked and convulsed under the indomitable mob of the orc. Savage, bloodthirsty creatures, they are without number, staining nearly every corner of the globe.

The mighty Orc Tzar, newest leader of the mob, marches ever north to find the lost organ of a forgotten god. Only a lone one-eyed orc with a mysterious gift can find the key to breaking the cycle forever...

Collects Orc Stain #1-5.
name: TPB Volume One

description: The newest ongoing series from HOMAGE COMICS unites two of comics' most acclaimed creators, Hate's Peter Bagge and Love & Rockets' Gilbert Hernandez, for the all-ages story of an all-girl band that's become the biggest thing in outer space, but can't catch a break on their home planet...Earth. Join Woo Woo, Honey and Krazy (and their always enthusiastic manager, Crusty) as they tour outer space via interstellar limo, rehearse in suburban New Jersey basements and try to convince home- planet audiences that they really have hit it big.
name: Everybody Say Yeah!
Walrus Blubber Sandwich

description: In issue #10 (featuring a lovely Buddy Bradley photo cover), Lisa is "The Nut" of the title who wrangles Buddy into getting her a job at the bookstore — with dire results.
name: The Nut

description: In the legendary second half of "Follow That Dream," Stinky becomes a grunge-rock hero, improving Buddy's sex life (see, he's Stinky's manager) while destroying all the other parts of his life (see, he's Stinky's manager).
name: Follow That Dream Part II

description: In part one of "Follow That Dream," Buddy and Stinky enter the wonderful world of Seattle grunge-rock as managers of a band; but this experience proves to be no nirvana, but an ever-tightening spiral of sleaze and insanity!
name: Follow That Dream

description: This is the cra-a-aziest issue yet of Peter Bagge's award-wining satirical comedy, as Black nerd George Hamilton III takes crackpot Lisa on a date!
name: Paranoia Rules Supreme!

description: Introducing two new characters: the parents of Buddy Bradley's girlfriend Valerie. Buddy and Valerie head to the 'burbs to visit the "in-laws," Valerie anticipating as usual the worst. But even she can't predict what happens!
name: Valerie's Parents

description: Stinky takes Buddy to visit a local hoarder and funny book afficionado. After rolling through some of the hits, Buddy gets into a rager of a fight initially over the gentleman styling Val and Lisa's hair, proving he might be an first class a-hole that we all love to hate.
name: Guys, Girls. Gays, ...and Buddy Bradley.

description: Buddy's little brother, Butch, comes to visit Seattle and he is one big mess. Share anxiety with Buddy as he takes his rather facist, tirelessly angry and angsty brother out to a party. Plus, a short story on 'Whatever Happened to Babs Bradley?"
name: Buddy Bradley is not his Brothers Keeper

description: Buddy and Valerie both take turns cataloguing their roommates' flaws and they all play out like a Greek tragedy when the two attempt to have a romantic spaghetti dinner at home. We each have a little of roommates George and Stinky and Lisa inside of us all, just hopefully not at the same time.
name: The Enigma That Is George Cecil Hamilton The Third

description: Buddy takes a deep look at his physical well-being but decides a drink and some billiards are the way to go, after all happy man is a healthy man. It's 'Hate at First Sight' when he meets Val. Buddy finds himself intrigued, smitten, enraged, cowed, and ultimately bedded (in the hospital!) by the quite attractive but weird and headstrong Val.
name: Hate at First Sight!

description: "Evil Eye" is a 12 issue comic series, written and illustrated by Richard Sala and published by Fantagraphics Books.
name: Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Chapter One
Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Part 3
Reflection in a Glass Scorpion (part four)

description: As the critically-acclaimed, Harvey-nominated series reaches its creepy and kooky sixth issue, the thrilling serial "Glass Scorpion" reaches its halfway point! Secrets are revealed, questions are answered and a certain villain realizes it's not such a good idea to kidnap Judy Drood, Girl Detective (and all-around loose cannon)! More mystery, murder and bloody black-humor fun than in any other current comic book series! The Hitchcockian, maze-like scenario and startlingly inventive set-pieces in this series should appeal to lovers of thrillers everywhere! Plus, in the same issue, find out more about the enigma known as Obscurus in the latest adventure featuring Evil Eye cover-girl Peculia!
name: Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Chapter 6
Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Chapter 5

description: Girl sleuth and all-around loose cannon Judy Drood finally meets up with the pirate girls! Will she be hypnotized by evil puppet Aunt Azalea into joining their ranks? Plus, in the same issue, cover-girl Peculia gets into a (literal?) catfight with a gang of feline assassins. Were they sent by Obscurus to kill her? Once again, Evil Eye manages to pack more mystery, murder and bloody black-humor into every issue than any other current comic book series. Its wild plot twists, inventive set-pieces and bizarre characters will appeal to lovers of thrillers everywhere!
name: Reflection in a Glass Scorpion 7

description: Now with upgraded Love and Rockets- and Eightball-style matte finish cardstock covers and full-color inside-covers! Judy Drood has been captured by the pirate girls and is brought before Aunt Azalea, who has some sinister plans for her. And, just when it seems things can't get worse for the two-fisted girl sleuth, she finds herself facing the murderous owner of the scorpion pin — the grotesque enigma known as Ms. Moss! In the same issue, cover girl Peculia becomes the object of desire for a monstrous menagerie of mole people! The critically acclaimed, Eisner-nominated series has developed a dedicated following who can't resist its intoxicating blend of humor and horror. This series, by multiple Harvey & Eisner nominee Richard Sala, continues to be surprising, exciting, sexy, spooky, compelling and addictive! "Don't be shy, buy the Eye!"
name: Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Eight
Reflection in a Glass Scorpion Part 9

description: The twelfth and final chapter of "Reflection in a Glass Scorpion," the epic graphic novel that has been serialized sinceEvil Eye #1 and has featured gruesome murders, girl pirates, an evil puppet, a mysterious tower and amateur sleuth Judy Drood. The black-humor horror thriller reaches its climax in the highest room of the campus clock tower where college student Kasper finds himself face to face with two-hundred-year-old murdering freak Massimo Ibex. Will Judy Drood arrive in time? Also in this issue, cover girl Peculia meets the brides of Dracula!
name: Evil Eye #12

description: Delphine is a four issue series by Richard Sala.
name: Delphine #1

description: "The Chuckling Whatsit" is a 200 page Graphic Novel written and illustrated by Richard Sala and published by Fantagraphics Books.
name: GN

description:
Adapted from the story by Christopher Reeve, Lawrence Konner & Mark Rosenthal and the screenplay by Lawrence Konner & Mark Rosenthal.

Superman seeks to create world peace by ridding the world of nuclear weapons, but inadvertently helps Lex Luthor create the fearsome Nuclear Man, a clone of the caped hero.

Notes:

  • 64 pages and no ads.
  • Based off the movie Superman IV: The Quest For Peace.
  • Comic book adaption contains scenes that were ultimately cut from the motion picture due to budget constrants.
name: The Quest For Peace

volume.name: Superman IV: The Quest For Peace

description: Meet the Exiles, a time-travelling mutant conglomerate dedicated to righting the wrongs of the Marvel Universe. Led by the teleporter Blink, from the Age of Apocalypse, this rag-tag group from alternate realities is guided by The Tallus, an instrument leading them from place to place in order to fulfill their missions of cosmic repair. Their early adventures lead them into confrontations with the Incredible Hulk, Wolverine and the X-Men.
name: Down the Rabbit Hole

description: The X-Men meet Quantum Leap in Wizard's one time "Book of the Month!" The quest continues as Blink's band struggles to survive their desperate directive to right the wrongs of the Marvel Multiverse - including battles with the Hulk and Galactus! Written by Pulitzer Prize-nominee Judd Winick and illustrated by Mike McKone with Jim Calafiore!
name: Volume 2

description: In "Woo Woo, Phone Home," the spaciest grrrl band this side of the Jersey Turnpike gets a taste of intergalactic glamour when they try living on a planet that actually loves their music! But the sweet smell of success turns sour when the alien atmosphere causes unexpected physiological changes in the girls, right before a big concert! Also, meet the missing alien who may have found a cozy home in a suspiciously familiar place back on Earth.
name: Woo-Woo Phone Home!
